' Methodology Diagram 02 — Witness → Promotion pipeline (sequence).
'
' Traces the canonical path from a generated witness to a permanent
' artifact (Rocq theorem / TLA⁺ invariant / Rust regression / ledger entry).
' Every machine-generated witness flows through this sequence; the
' classification step is the gate that prevents over- and under-claiming.
'
' Render:
'   plantuml -tsvg docs/theory/slashing/methodology/diagrams/02-witness-to-promotion.puml

@startuml 02-witness-to-promotion
!theme plain

skinparam ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam ParticipantBorderColor    #333333
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor       #FFE0B2
skinparam NoteBorderColor           #E65100
skinparam SequenceLifeLineBorderColor #444444
skinparam defaultFontName "sans-serif"
skinparam defaultFontSize 11

title Witness → Promotion pipeline (canonical trace)

participant "Search tool\n(Sage, Hypothesis,\nproptest, libFuzzer,\nKani, Loom, TLC)"  as Tool #FFF7EE
participant "Threat-model\nclassifier"        as Classifier #FFEBEE
participant "Rust production\nreproduction"   as Reproduce  #EEF2FF
participant "Traceability\nledger"             as Ledger    #EEFAF1
participant "Action engine\n(per status)"      as Action    #EEFAF1
participant "Mechanized artifact\n(Rocq / TLA⁺ / Kani)"   as Mechanized #EEF2FF
participant "Rust regression\nor anchor"       as Regression #FFF7EE
participant "Persistent corpus\n(fuzz/, hypothesis_persistent_corpus, …)"  as Corpus #EEFAF1

== Step 1 — Witness generation ==
Tool -[#E65100]-> Classifier: witness w (with metadata)
note right of Tool
  Tool emits w with seed, kind,
  search parameters, and observed
  property violation.
end note

== Step 2 — Threat-model classification ==
Classifier -[#1565C0]-> Classifier: assign class (one of 6)
note right of Classifier
  bisimilar | permitted_bug_fix |
  candidate_boundary | projection_risk |
  assumption_counterexample |
  unexpected  ← must reclassify
end note

== Step 3 — Production reproduction ==
Classifier -[#1565C0]-> Reproduce: replay w on Rust path

alt witness reproduces
    Reproduce -[#C62828]-> Ledger: status = confirmed_current_bug
else witness rejected by production
    Reproduce -[#1565C0]-> Ledger: status = not_reproduced_in_rust
else guarded by production check
    Reproduce -[#1565C0]-> Ledger: status = projection_risk_guarded
else theorem precondition is necessary
    Reproduce -[#1565C0]-> Ledger: status = assumption_counterexample
else suggests stronger theorem
    Reproduce -[#1565C0]-> Ledger: status = proof_or_model_strengthening
else inconclusive
    Reproduce -[#E65100]-> Ledger: status = needs_source_audit
end

== Step 4 — Action ==
Ledger -[#1565C0]-> Action: lookup status → action

alt confirmed_current_bug
    Action -[#C62828]-> Regression: write pre_fix_bug_N.rs
    Action -[#C62828]-> Mechanized: update Rocq / TLA⁺ if normative
    Action -[#2E7D32]-> Regression: fix source + add post-fix anchor
else confirmed_fixed_bug
    Action -[#1565C0]-> Regression: keep pre_fix_bug_N.rs
else proof_or_model_strengthening
    Action -[#2E7D32]-> Mechanized: promote to Rocq theorem / TLA⁺ invariant
    Action -[#2E7D32]-> Regression: add prop_t_*.rs
else assumption_counterexample
    Action -[#2E7D32]-> Mechanized: strengthen precondition
    Action -[#1565C0]-> Regression: add theorem_assumption_counterexamples.rs entry
else not_reproduced_in_rust | model_boundary
    Action -[#1565C0]-> Ledger: record only (no source change)
end

== Step 5 — Persistence ==
Action -[#1565C0]-> Corpus: append minimized fixture
Corpus -[#1565C0]-> Tool: replay on next CI run

== Step 6 — Loop closure ==
Action -[#1565C0]-> Tool: re-run; verify w no longer surfaces\n(or surfaces with expected post-fix status)

note over Tool, Corpus
  The pipeline is monotone: every iteration either expands the
  ledger (new finding), expands the mechanized arm (new theorem
  or invariant), or expands the corpus (new replayable fixture).
  No finding is ever silently dropped.
end note

@enduml
